'''Carnival Week''' was an annual week-long celebration on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. It is unknown when the tradition began, but during the reign of [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] it grew to become an outlandish event that included [[Imperial Military/Legends|military]] parades, orbital [[Fireworks/Legends|fireworks]] displays and [[Execution Channel|public executions]] of the [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor's]] political enemies. The celebration drew an exceptional number of offworlders to Coruscant and was an event [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] citizens saved their [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] for all [[Galactic Standard Calendar|year]].

Its persistence after [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] [[Death/Legends|death]] is unknown.

